      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were drawn from a single production lot and tested across two independent laboratories. Sample size and lot traceability satisfy the required level for medium model risk."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level; multiple test conditions would be needed to reach level 3.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted at a single load configuration (compression-bending at the prescribed F1717 offset). Variation across multiple load angles or axial offsets was not explored, limiting the achieved level to 2, one below the required level of 3. This is a documented shortfall."
